<DOC><DOCNO> ZF32-017-380 </DOCNO><DOCID>11 568 871</DOCID><JOURNAL>Computergram International  Nov 1 1991 n1796* Full Text COPYRIGHT Apt Data Services (UK) 1991.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Aimtech launches release 4.0 of its Iconauthor authoring systemfor Windows. (Product Announcement)andM;</TITLE><DESCRIPT>Company:   AimTech Corp. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   IconAuthor 4.0 (Multimedia software) (Product introduction)Microsoft Windows 3.0 (Graphical user interface) (Computerprograms).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionMultimedia softwareAuthoringGraphical user interface.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>AIMTECH LAUNCHES RELEASE 4.0 OF ITS ICONAUTHORandM;AUTHORING SYSTEM FOR WINDOWSandM;Aimtech Corp, based in London in the UK, has launched its authoring systemIconAuthor 4.0.andP;  The use of the Microsoft Corp Windows 3.0 environment isintended to enable non-programmers to create multimedia applications in areassuch as computer-based training, information and transaction-based kiosks andinteractive business presentations.andP;  Non-programmers, it says, can develop amultimedia presentation by building structure and content.andP;  To buildstructure, icons that represent computer functions are moved from an iconlibrary and connected into a flow chart that depicts the logic of theapplication.andP;  Presentation content, including text, graphics, animation, fullmotion video and audio, is then added to the icon structure via dialogueboxes.andP;  IconAuthor 4.0 runs under MS-DOS 3.1 or higher as well as underDigital Equipment Corp VMS and Ultrix under DECwindows.andP;  It requires an 80286or 80386 processor, 1Mb of RAM for 16 colour graphics or 2Mb of RAM for 256colour graphics and uses CGA, EGA, VGA or super VGA graphics boards.andO;IconAuthor supports multimedia peripherals such as video disk and tapeplayers, video overlay cards and audio systems that run under Windows.andP;  It iscompatible with dBase and communicates with data management applications.andO;IconAuthor supports Dynamic Data Exchange, Dynamic Link Libraries, andmultimedia extensions for Windows.andP;  David Hendon, general manager of Aimtech,says that users are currently upgrading from IconAuthor 3.0 to 4.0.andP;  He saidthat DEC is testing an IconAuthor RISC version under Ultrix using DECwindowsand that a version is being developed for VMS and Ultrix.andP;  He expects thatIconAuthor will be available on Data General Corp's AViiONs under Unix and XWindow, and under Hewlett-Packard Co's HP-UX within 90 days.andP;  An OS/2 versionis planned for the first quarter of 1992.andP;  IconAuthor 4.0 is available nowand costs #2,600.andO;</TEXT></DOC>